f=Engineering/axiom/custom/complexity-analysis/SKILL.md · in=complexity-analysis axiom's rigor: honest time space bounds worst, average, amortized algorithms department ships, reasoning justifies bound honesty say asymptotic class wrong thing optimize. supplies numbers dsa-design-records states flags algorithmic regressions code review catch. · p="It's fast enough" scaling problems hide. O(n²) that's fine n=100 melts n=100,000, nobody noticed because nobody analyzed it. Rigorous complexity analysis makes scaling behavior explicit before production finds and, equally, stops premature optimization O(n) runs n=10. · wu=Triggers: "what's complexity," "will scale," "is O(n²)," nested loop over request-sized data, recursive call, review flag algorithmic cost, any dsa-design-record needing bounds. · st:/ Protocol=`An algorithm / code path to analyze \· -> Identify the input(s) whose size drives cost (n, and any second dimension m) \· -> Count the dominant operations as a function of n (loops, recursion depth × work, structure ops) \· -> State time: worst / average / amortized (where they differ, all that matter) \· State space: auxiliary + input, incl. recursion stack` · in=**Name input dimension(s).** Cost function something request count, payload size, graph nodes×edges. Two-dimensional inputs items, each) get both; collapsing them hides real cost. **Worst, average, amortized ones matter.** hash lookup average-O(1), worst-O(n) under collisions; quicksort average-O(n log n), worst-O(n²). State ones bear decision, conditions trigger bad case worst case "never happens" what adversary triggers (ties cypher's DoS class). **Space counts stack.** Auxiliary space includes recursion depth; elegant recursion O(n) space loop makes O(1). Say so. **Justify, don't assert.** bound carries derivation recurrence solved, loops counted, amortization argument. asserted bound uncheckable rots (dsa-design-records' rule). **Asymptotics honesty.** Big-O describes large system's small, constant factors dominate, say asymptotic improvement isn't worth route performance-profiling real measurement. Premature optimization cold paths cost, virtue (dev's boring-is-a-feature). **Flag regressions.** change worsens hot path's complexity class (O(log O(n)) review finding, surfaced dev's code review even "passes tests" tests small won't catch it. · of=`## Complexity: [algorithm / path] \· Input dimensions: [n = …, m = …] \· Time: worst O(…) [when: …] \· average O(…) \· amortized O(…) — because [derivation] \· Space: O(…) auxiliary incl. [stack?] — because […] \· At this system's n (~[value]): [asymptotic dominates / constants dominate → profile]` · pr=**Cost function named dimension** collapsing dimensions hides it., **State worst case what triggers it** "impossible" case attack (DoS)., **Space includes stack** recursion isn't free., **Every bound derived, asserted** unjustified O() unverifiable., **Asymptotics honesty** small means measure, optimize; Big-O about large, **Complexity regressions findings** tests small won't catch them. · f=Bound genuinely hard derive (complex recurrence, data-dependent) give best honest analysis uncertainty MEASURE (performance-profiling) rather assert; label reasoning-based (rule 0.6)., Input distribution unknown state worst-case note average depends distribution; don't assume uniform silently., "Fast enough" claimed without analysis provide analysis; "fast enough current valid conclusion once bound stated. · b:with Other Skills=**dsa-design-records** (sibling) states bounds derives; **performance-profiling** (sibling) measures asymptotics don't settle it., **dev/code-review-standards**: complexity regressions route review findings., **cypher/attack-playbooks**: worst-case triggers axiom identifies DoS surfaces cypher tests (L10 unbounded consumption)., **raj dana**: hot-path query complexity their consumers' concerns.